Rakuen's Covenant Council maintains an open cartography commission for any expedition-grade survey of the Cinderteeth Mountains. The range has never been systematically mapped: its eight distinct geological zones span from foothills Ashfang remnant territory through volcanic caldera, and the Ventspeaker refugees confirm that significant portions of the interior have shifted since the last partial survey attempt. Chart every accessible room in the range and return a complete navigation record suitable for refugee route planning and Covenant research.
Your Cinderteeth Mountains survey is complete and the Covenant Council has filed your cartography packet in the refugee route planning archive. The Council's registrar notes this is the first complete survey of the range in living memory and that several zones previously marked as impassable in old records are now documented as navigable with appropriate preparation. The Ventspeaker refugee committee has already begun marking provisional return-route options from your grid.

